        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 3 at 1:24PM PDT by NWS Elko NV</headline>
        <description>At 123 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 11
miles southwest of Tuscarora, moving north at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Heavy rainfall along with gusty winds that could knock
down tree limbs and blow around unsecured objects. Minor
hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Willow Creek Reservoir.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
